frameDefinitions: A Protagonist changes the overall position and posture of the body.
One phenomenon, the Predictive_phenomenon is an indication of the future or current (but still uncertain) existence of another phenomenon, the Future_phenomenon.
An Agent supports their body in a particular Location.
A Place is located far off from centers of population, culture, and/or trade.
An Agent matches location with an Entity in order to fulfill some  Purpose.
frameExamples: Smithers <t>leaned</t> forward to grab the folder on the far side.
I ca n't remember how many times he <t>visited</t> ! DNI
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Protagonist</fen> changes posture.
<fen>Predictive_phenomenon</fen> provides evidence for the existence or the nature of the <fen>Outcome</fen> of <fen>Future_phenomenon</fen>.
<fen>Future_phenomenon</fen> is that phenomenon that is predicted to occur or have a particular quality.
The role <fen>Outcome</fen> identifies those expressions that indicate how the <fen>Future_phenomenon</fen> is expected to turn out based on the evidence of the <fen>Predictive_phenomenon</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the omen is occuring.
The location where something good or bad might occur.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the individual whose body is in a particular posture.  The <fen>Agent</fen> role is generally expressed as the external argument of verbs:
A description of the position of the <fen>Agent</fen>.  The <fen>Location</fen> of the <fen>Agent</fen> is frequently expressed and generally occurs as a PP Complement:
The part of the body that provides support to the <fen>Agent</fen>'s body in the posture.
This role indicates the Time interval during which the <fen>Agent</fen> held a certain posture.
The town or area that is in a remote location.
The sentient entity that is temporarily with the <fen>Entity</fen> in order to fulfil some <fen>Purpose</fen>.

The physical entity that is permanently associated with entities or characteristics that the <fen>Agent</fen> wishes to use for some <fen>Purpose</fen>.  During the visit, the <fen>Agent</fen> matches location with the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The time at which a visit is made.
A description of the position of the <fen>Agent</fen> during the visit.
listRoleExamples: <fex>To achieve so much this year</fex> augurs well for the future.
This move presages <fex>a freeze on the granting of new concessions</fex>.
It all bodes <fex>well</fex> for the future.
The storm bodes ill for you <fex>here</fex> .
I stood <fex>on my heels</fex> and looked out the window
<fex>Yesterday evening</fex> he was sitting in his armchair as usual
He lives in the <fex><t>backwoods</t></fex> of Canada.
